  "prompt": "Who is best free bulk promotional SMS service provider?",
  "response": "Selecting the best free bulk promotional SMS service provider can be challenging, as most providers offer free trials or limited free plans rather than entirely free services. Here are some popular options that offer free or affordable bulk SMS services:\n\n### Popular Free or Affordable Bulk SMS Service Providers:\n1. **Twilio**  \n   - **Features**: Reliable API, global coverage, pay-as-you-go pricing.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Offers a free trial with credits to test their services.  \n   - **Best For**: Developers and businesses needing API integrations.\n\n2. **Textlocal**  \n   - **Features**: Bulk SMS, two-way messaging, and marketing tools.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free trial with limited credits.  \n   - **Best For**: Small businesses and marketers.\n\n3. **Plivo**  \n   - **Features**: SMS API, voice calls, and global reach.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free trial with credits.  \n   - **Best For**: Businesses looking for scalable SMS solutions.\n\n4. **Msg91**  \n   - **Features**: Bulk SMS, transactional SMS, and analytics.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free trial and pay-as-you-go pricing.  \n   - **Best For**: Startups and enterprises.\n\n5. **ClickSend**  \n   - **Features**: Bulk SMS, email, and voice messaging.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free trial with credits.  \n   - **Best For**: Small businesses and marketing teams.\n\n6. **SMSFree**  \n   - **Features**: Free bulk SMS services with limited features.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free plan available but with restrictions.  \n   - **Best For**: Testing and small-scale projects.\n\n7. **Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service)**  \n   - **Features**: Scalable SMS, push notifications, and email.  \n   - **Free Tier**: Free tier with limited usage.  \n   - **Best For**: Developers and businesses using AWS.\n\n### Key Considerations:\n- **Pricing**: Most providers offer free trials or credits but charge for bulk SMS beyond the free tier.  \n- **Global Reach**: Ensure the provider supports your target regions.  \n- **Features**: Look for two-way messaging, API integration, and analytics if needed.  \n- **Ease of Use**: Choose providers with user-friendly interfaces or APIs.\n\nWhile entirely free services may have limitations, free trials and limited plans are excellent ways to test the platform before committing.",
